President Trump made remarks aboard Air Force One, highlighting a trade deal between the United States and China. He stated that the deal, if it happens, would be one of the largest deals ever made and would have a positive impact on various industries, including farming and technology. Trump also mentioned that China would be opening up its markets and reducing tariffs. Additionally, he discussed his good relationship with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and their agreement to work together on North Korea. Trump praised Kim's commitment to cracking down on the illegal drug fentanyl, which is causing problems in the United States. The President also mentioned plans for a summit with Kim in January or February, without specifying the location. Furthermore, Trump stated that he would be formally terminating the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) in the near future, with the option for Congress to approve the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) instead. He criticized NAFTA for causing unemployment and negative economic effects for the US.